comments.body:
> @taylor-yamashita it looks like they've accounted for this issue in reform... I'm not sure exactly how it all hooks up. Maybe it's this coercion require? https://trailblazer.to/2.1/docs/reform.html#reform-options-coercion

I did try this approach (it uses Types::Form::DateTime instead of Types::Params::DateTime) but wasn't able to resolve the issue.

Update: Worked with @eliotjordan and decided that coercion wasn't working. Reworked the validator to validate with `DateTime.strptime()` and `rescue Date::Error` instead of coercion. (With the coercion approach, invalid dates would get caught up in a changeset error before any of the validation could happen.)

Note: the existing numismatics accessions entries all have differently formatted dates; this change will only affect newly created entries and edits to old ones.
This will require a followup date cleanup migration to standardize all existing numismatic accessions date formats.

princeton_ansible.title: Create Playbook for Byzantine Translations Project

comments.body:
- [x] Obtain database dump from libphp-prod, site is located in /var/www/apps/byzantine on the machine. The unix user that is the owner of the directory is called "drupal" not deploy. 
- [x] Test site locally on Drupal 8 https://github.com/pulibrary/byzantine_translations/issues/18
- [x] Add new proxy rule to lib-adc for new staging staging server
- [x] Test playbook on new staging environment
- [x] Load database in staging environment
- [ ] Test playbook on new production environment
- [ ] Load database in production environment
- [ ] Preview Site in new production environment
- [ ] Update existing proxy pass rule for production URL in lib-adc to point new production server.

Still struggling with the tests not passing. 

Also, how should we get the logos on the servers? For the staging server, I manually copied them into the `/var/www/byzantine/shared` directory and changed their owner and permissions to:

```bash
-rw-rw---- 1 www-data deploy  1438 Feb 23 17:32 favicon_0_0.ico
-rw-rw---- 1 www-data deploy 25860 Feb 23 17:32 firestone-small.png
-rw-rw---- 1 www-data deploy  5830 Feb 23 17:32 hp_logo.jpg
-rw-rw---- 1 www-data deploy   527 Feb 23 17:32 pul-logo.gif
```

I think using the shared directory for the images makes sense. These are the only file assets this site will need to use. Having them available in Drupal's sites/default/files directory in this fashion is less involved than setting up a mount point on a fileshare (which is what we've done for sites that that all for the uploading of file assets).
Is it ok if we put them in the byzantine translations github repository? It looks like that's how the library site does it.
